---
import BaseHead from "@/components/BaseHead.astro";
import CaseBoard from "@/components/case-file/CaseBoard.astro";
import CaseTimeline from "@/components/case-file/CaseTimeline.astro";
import { longIslandCase } from "@/data/cases/longIsland";
import { caseFileToTimeline } from "@/data/cases/utils";

export const prerender = true;

const title = "The Long Island Murders";
const summary =
  "An interactive case board of the Long Island murder victims, from 1993 to the Gilgo Beach discoveries and the charges that came decades later.";
const pubDate = new Date("2026-07-07");
const ogImage = "/posts/true-crime/mapping-the-long-island-murder-victims/thumb@2x.jpg";

const victimCount = longIslandCase.people.filter((p) => p.role === "victim").length;
const record = caseFileToTimeline(longIslandCase, { hrefFor: (event) => `#t:${event.id}` });
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en" class="dark">
  <head>
    <BaseHead title={title} description={summary} image={ogImage} type="blogpost" datePublished={pubDate} />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Archivo:wdth,wght@62..125,100..900&family=Fragment+Mono&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
    <link href="https://api.mapbox.com/mapbox-gl-js/v2.15.0/mapbox-gl.css" rel="stylesheet" />
  </head>
  <body class="cp">
    <header class="cp-nav">
      <a href="/">dandenney.com</a>
      <a href="/posts/true-crime/mapping-the-long-island-murder-victims">Read the original 2020 article</a>
    </header>

    <section class="cp-hero">
      <p class="cp-meta">
        <span>Case board</span>
        <span>Suffolk County, NY</span>
        <span>1993–2024</span>
      </p>
      <h1 class="cp-title">The Long Island<br />Murders</h1>
      <div class="cp-lede">
        <p>
          "The Long Island Serial Killer" is a misnomer. The more you look at Long Island from the early 90s until the
          2010s, the worse it gets: {victimCount - 1} murder victims and one highly debated death, a convicted killer
          who went unconnected for twenty years, and an arrest that didn't come until 2023.
        </p>
        <p>
          The board below holds the timeline of events and the people at the center of them. Move through it in order,
          or select a person to see their story and their places on the map. They are people, like you and me, and
          their stories deserve to be told.
        </p>
      </div>
      <p class="cp-hint" aria-hidden="true">↓</p>
    </section>

    <CaseBoard caseFile={longIslandCase} />

    <section class="cp-record">
      <header class="cp-record-head">
        <p class="cp-kicker">Chronology</p>
        <h2>The record</h2>
        <p>
          Thirty-one years of the case in one place. Select any entry to open it on the board above.
        </p>
      </header>
      <CaseTimeline groups={record} />
    </section>

    <section class="cp-outro">
      <div class="cp-outro-col">
        <h2>Yet to be solved</h2>
        <p>
          The patterns changed over time, which only leads to questions. The early victims were subjected to aggressive
          violence and left in a specific pose. The next four were dismembered and discovered in multiple locations.
          The Gilgo Four were found in a single place, laid to rest in a similar way. Was there one killer who
          escalated and then de-escalated, or multiple killers acting in the same area? Joel Rifkin, Robert Shulman,
          and John Bittrolff were each killing people on Long Island between 1991 and 1993, so the answer is not
          obvious. We won't know until the killer of at least one of the remaining victims is apprehended.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you haven't yet heard the stories of the Long Island victims, I strongly recommend
          <a href="https://www.aetv.com/shows/the-killing-season">The Killing Season</a>, where you'll meet family and
          friends of many of the people on this board.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="cp-outro-col">
        <h2>If you know something</h2>
        <p>
          Some of the victims still have no name, and some of the murders have no answer. If you have any information,
          please share it on the <a href="https://www.gilgonews.com/SubmitATip">Gilgo News tip site</a>.
        </p>
        <h2>About this page</h2>
        <p>
          This is a rebuild of an <a href="/posts/true-crime/mapping-the-long-island-murder-victims">article I made in
          2020</a>, which was later listed among the articles viewed in the Rex Heuermann bail documentation. Locations
          are approximate. Sources and further reading are in the original article.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <footer class="cp-footer">
      <a href="/">dandenney.com</a>
      <span>Made with care for the victims and their families</span>
    </footer>

    <script is:inline src="https://api.mapbox.com/mapbox-gl-js/v2.15.0/mapbox-gl.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  :root {
    color-scheme: dark;
  }

  .cp {
    margin: 0;
    background: #0b0d12;
    color: #e9ebef;
    font-family: "Archivo", system-ui, sans-serif;
  }

  .cp a {
    color: inherit;
    text-decoration-color: rgba(233, 235, 239, 0.35);
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    transition: text-decoration-color 200ms ease;
  }

  .cp a:hover {
    text-decoration-color: #e3a94f;
  }

  .cp-nav {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 1rem;
    padding: 1.25rem clamp(1rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    font-family: "Fragment Mono", ui-monospace, monospace;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  }

  .cp-nav a {
    text-decoration: none;
    color: #a3abba;
  }

  .cp-nav a:hover {
    color: #e9ebef;
  }

  /* ---------- Hero ---------- */

  .cp-hero {
    padding: clamp(3rem, 9vh, 6.5rem) clamp(1rem, 4vw, 3rem) clamp(2.5rem, 7vh, 5rem);
    max-width: 78rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .cp-meta {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.5rem 1.75rem;
    margin: 0 0 1.75rem;
    font-family: "Fragment Mono", ui-monospace, monospace;
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #a3abba;
  }

  .cp-meta span + span {
    position: relative;
  }

  .cp-meta span + span::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    left: -1rem;
    top: 50%;
    width: 3px;
    height: 3px;
    border-radius: 999px;
    translate: 0 -50%;
    background: #666e7d;
  }

  .cp-title {
    margin: 0 0 2.25rem;
    font-size: clamp(3rem, 11vw, 8.5rem);
    font-weight: 870;
    font-variation-settings: "wdth" 118;
    line-height: 0.94;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .cp-lede {
    max-width: 62ch;
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .cp-lede p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 1.5vw, 1.125rem);
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: #c3c9d4;
  }

  .cp-hint {
    margin: 3rem 0 0;
    font-family: "Fragment Mono", ui-monospace, monospace;
    color: #666e7d;
    animation: cp-drift 2.4s ease-in-out infinite;
  }

  @keyframes cp-drift {
    0%, 100% { transform: translateY(0); }
    50% { transform: translateY(6px); }
  }

  /* ---------- The record ---------- */

  .cp-record {
    max-width: 62rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: clamp(3.5rem, 9vh, 6.5rem) clamp(1rem, 4vw, 3rem) clamp(1.5rem, 4vh, 3rem);
  }

  .cp-kicker {
    margin: 0 0 0.9rem;
    font-family: "Fragment Mono", ui-monospace, monospace;
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #666e7d;
  }

  .cp-record-head {
    margin-bottom: clamp(2.25rem, 5vh, 3.5rem);
  }

  .cp-record-head h2 {
    margin: 0 0 0.9rem;
    font-size: clamp(1.9rem, 4vw, 2.6rem);
    font-weight: 820;
    font-variation-settings: "wdth" 112;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    line-height: 1;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .cp-record-head p:last-child {
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 58ch;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: #a3abba;
  }

  /* ---------- Outro ---------- */

  .cp-outro {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(320px, 1fr));
    gap: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 4.5rem);
    max-width: 78rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: clamp(3rem, 8vh, 5.5rem) clamp(1rem, 4vw, 3rem);
  }

  .cp-outro h2 {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    font-weight: 780;
    font-variation-settings: "wdth" 110;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .cp-outro h2 + p + h2 {
    margin-top: 2.25rem;
  }

  .cp-outro p {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    max-width: 58ch;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: #a3abba;
  }

  .cp-footer {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 1rem;
    padding: 1.5rem clamp(1rem, 4vw, 3rem) 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(233, 235, 239, 0.12);
    font-family: "Fragment Mono", ui-monospace, monospace;
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: #666e7d;
  }

  .cp-footer a {
    color: #a3abba;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .cp-footer a:hover {
    color: #e9ebef;
  }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .cp-hint {
      animation: none;
    }
  }
</style>
